<b>Regen Stacking - </b>11/6/01 10:54:23 AM<br>~ <b>Roliel Glorysong</b><blockquote>You can stack this song with Niv's Melody of Preservation for an insanely high regen rate. With my maestro lute, I can get a regen of about 40 a tick. I grouped with a shaman friend of mine, and he was able to get a regen rate of 120 a tick with the songs, regen items, a regen spell, and inherant iksar regen.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Yes it stacks - </b>8/16/01 2:54:55 PM<br>~ <b>Kasreyn Giantharrow</b><blockquote>Repeat after me, class:  Level 32 Clarity stacks with everything because it's not a question of stacking.<br><br>Think of it as a 32nd level DD song (like Dirge or either of the BBB songs) which does negative mana damage.  Basically, every time the song pulses it adds mana to the supply of anyone in range.  What that means is that since the Cantatas (should change that as VI has, Kocho ;) are icon-based, persistent &quot;spell&quot; effects in the same &quot;spell line&quot; as Hymn, they won't stack with it or each other.  To provide emergency mana in a pinch, twist 1 Cantata with 2 CCCs for maximum output.<br><br></blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Awesome - </b>8/3/01 8:13:38 AM<br>~ <b>Strandlee</b><blockquote>This song is amazing, when you get it you can ditch both the 32 mana song and the pure heal song altogether.   Not sure what the mana or stamina regen is, but with a Lute of the Gypsy Princess it regens 25 HP standing.  I think I have meleed maybe once since I got this song it's that good twisted.  SKs and pallies will tell you they are amazed their mana never seems to drop when fighting (from stuns, ED, etc) and clerics will tell you it's at least as good as C2 if not better. This song was a great reward for reaching a high level IMO.<br><br>Lexicus Magnavin<br>55 Troubadour of MT</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Stamina regen - </b>6/27/01 6:44:25 AM<br>~ <b>Anon</b><blockquote>The stamina regen of this song is weird. It doesn't seem to speed up the recovery (it took me 50 secs standing to regen from 0 stamina to full, whether I was playing song or not), but yet if you were fighting 15 mobs, one after another, while playing this song, your stamina would never go down. I wonder why...<br><br>Also, can this song be stacked with our original lvl 32 clarity for faster mana regeneration? I'm sure this question has been asked 100 times, but yet I can't find a nice answer...</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
